name: Hole in the Ground
description: It doesn't seem like much more than a simple hole in the ground.

name: Abandoned Cave
description: Whatever used to live her has long-since left.

name: Hidden Cave
description: You are surprised to find a cave entrance hidden behind the waterfall.

name: Small Cave
description: Looks like you should be in and out before dark.

name: Small Dungeon
description: Not just small in length, this dungeon has very low ceilings.

name: Cave at the Edge of Town
description: A well known cave at the outskirts of civilization.

name: Abandoned Dungeon
description: This dungeon has fallen into disrepair.

name: Lost Dungeon
description: You'd heard stories of this place, but never thought you'd find it.

name: The Wilds
description: Led by the dire bear, Rend, beasts of all types roam the area, a danger to merchants and travelers.

name: Goblin Camp
description: A bounty has been placed on Geebo, a leader of a group of goblins in the woods.

name: Kobold Attack!
description: Tig the Mighty is leading a group of kobolds against a group of miners! They need your help!

name: Rebel Hideout
description: Reports suggest rebels and thieves, led by Honor Reagh, have expanded their base of operations.

name: Haunted Graveyard
description: Stories tell of dead things, like Rattleneck the skeleton, rising from their graves to devour the living.

name: Infested Mines
description: Evil permeates what remains of a once-prominent silver mine.

name: Abandoned Mine
description: This mine is no longer operating.

name: Hidden Mine
description: The owner of this mine was surely hoping no one would ever find it.

name: Lost Mine
description: Supposedly many workers were lost along with the mine.

name: Spellplagued Caves
description: The devastation of the spellplague has spread to all corners of the land.

name: Hidden Dungeon
description: Your map says the entrance should be under a rock shaped like a wolf...

name: Cave of Mushrooms
description: Fungi cover every surface of this dank place.

name: Cave of Filth
description: Signs of pestilence can be seen miles from the mouth of the cave.

name: Bandit Campground
description: Bandits have moved into the area, assuming no one would look for them here.

name: Spiral Mines
description: They seem to go on for ever...

name: Den of Alphas
description: Powerful beasts of all shapes and sizes follow the actions of The Snarl, a cunning dire wolf.

name: Goblin Caves
description: If the goblin leader, Droolmouf, can be defeated, the remaining goblins should scatter.

name: Kobold Lair
description: Meklit Spordlik has been leading a kobold uprising. He was last spotted in this general area.

name: Rebel Command
description: The supposed mastermind behind the theft of the Crown of Neverwinter, Karzov, is known to be in this area.

name: Burial Grounds
description: The walls of this ancient place are lined with the bones of the dead.

name: Orc Camp
description: The time has come to drive the orcs, led by Makred the Foul, back to wherever they came from.

name: Gnoll Hideout
description: Festersnout has led a large group of gnolls to an abandoned mine that they've adopted as their own.

name: Spider Infestation
description: A local mine has been experiencing an extreme number of spider attacks recently. Some even speak of a spider known as Valindra's Pet.

name: The Sewers
description: Word has spread that Varin Chalgash has brought wererats to the sewers under a small town.

name: Haunted Forest
description: The undead plague the woods. A hero is needed to brave the wilds and defeat the skeletal archer known as Deadeye.

name: Dungeon of Blades
description: Though you can guess, you're not entirely sure why it's called the Dungeon of Blades...

name: Fighting Pit
description: Glory awaits the brave!

name: Misty Caves
description: An unnatural mist floats from the mouth of the cave.

name: Unstable Mines
description: Each step sends tremors that could mean total collapse.

name: Dungeon Below Town
description: Whenever the innkeeper gets a few drinks in him, he spins tales of a dungeon that runs underneath the entire expanse of the city.

name: Underground Canal
description: It's a dirty job, but somebody's got to do it.

name: Abandoned Catacombs
description: The dead do not like to be disturbed.

name: Haunted Cave
description: Ghosts of the past are said to haunt this cave.

name: Haunted Dungeon
description: The spirits of failed adventurers are said to roam these halls.

name: Haunted Mines
description: A tragic collapse took the lives of hundreds of workers, many of whom are believed to haunt the place still.

name: Orc Stronghold
description: Orcs led by Kartok Paingiver have turned an old, abandoned dungeon into a fortified stronghold.

name: Gnoll Caves
description: The gnolls' main breeding grounds have been discovered, a bounty placed in the leader, One-Fang.

name: Spider Nest
description: Cobwebs surround the mouth of the cave, showing signature weaving patterns of the dreadful Daughter of Lolth.

name: Wererat Den
description: Southpaw's wererats have accidentally created an easy-to-follow trail back to their primary breeding ground.

name: Midnight
description: Some say you can see the ashen glow of Scorch down in the catacombs when the clock strikes 12.

name: Cavern of Dark Rituals
description: Mizreal Everdark and her ashmadai followers have been performing unholy rituals in a nearby cave system.

name: Lizardfolk Camp
description: A blackscale brute known as Slickskin has led a tribe of lizardfolk to a nearby swamp.

name: Troll Caves
description: Bring as much fire and acid as you can carry when visiting troll-infested caves. Bring double for Hurlan Rockbiter.

name: Full Moon
description: Thunderhowl's terrifying roar can be heard for miles whenever the moon is full.

name: Abandoned Stockades
description: The Feared is among the long-dead prisoners that have risen back to a state of undeath within the old stockades.

name: Haunted Catacombs
description: The dead walk these halls... Or so the story goes.

name: Tomb of Pain
description: A true sadist built the traps and implements found within these walls.

name: Haunted Tomb
description: Tortured souls roam this tomb, waiting for the day they can visit the land of the living.

name: Twisted Catacombs
description: By the time you leave this place, your mind will be as twisted as the spirits that corrupt it.

name: Rotting Caves
description: Chunks of the wall seem to crumble and rot as you approach.

name: Oozing Depths
description: Slime rises up and out of the bottomless darkness.

name: Buried Ruins
description: Though it's believed the ruins were buried by natural events, some scholars suggest the tragedy was magically triggered.

name: Cave of Wonder
description: Entrance to this place is barred to all but the truly worthy.

name: Dungeon of Murk
description: This place is akin to an underground swamp.

name: Cave of Sadness
description: Even the walls seem to cry out in despair.

name: Ashmadai Temple
description: The night sky flooded with dark, hellish magic, indicates Rohini the Prophet has reached an ashmadai temple.

name: The Swamp
description: Lizardfolk have completely taken over the swamplands, The Scalefather instrumental in their ever increasing numbers.

name: Troll Lair
description: The fell troll, Marpog Grumblegut, has taken over a nearby cavern. Other trolls have started to move in as well.

name: Werewolf Den
description: Packmaster Zayev has claimed this cave as a haven for werewolves, confident no hunter would dare step foot inside.

name: Haunted Armory
description: The spirits of dead soldiers and thugs use the discarded weaponry to wage their war against the living, Ironbones chief among them.

name: Misty Mines
description: It is believed an ancient civilization was discovered deep in these mines.

name: Cave of Voices
description: Whispers from the walls. Whispers that can dominate the weak.

name: Tomb of Spirits
description: Spirits roam free in this place, some benevolent, some malicious.

name: Tomb of Forgotten Gods
description: Unholy names have been carved into the walls, waiting to be read aloud.

name: Mines of Madness
description: Most workers would only last for a few days before being driven insane.

name: Cavern of Death
description: No one has ever visited this place and returned to tell the tale.

name: The Maw
description: The entrance to this dungeon has been carved into the shape of a demonic mouth.

name: Cave of Skulls
description: Built of bone and flesh, few are brave enough to enter.

name: The Ironworks
description: Many of the realm's weapons and armor were forged here.

name: Pit of Despair
description: Light cannot penetrate beyond the mouth of the cave.

name: Cave of Nightmares
description: The impossible and grotesque call this place home.

name: Dungeon of Horrors
description: Your deepest fears made flesh.

name: Waking Nightmare
description: Tell yourself this is only a dream and A'dryx'l the Overseer and his abominations aren't real...

name: Frozen Caves
description: Murgal Mawcram, and other creatures adapted to the ice and snow, hide within these caves.

name: Living Mine
description: Bards tell impossible stories of a place where the walls and torches come to life and follow the orders of General Ignazar.

name: Shadow Forest
description: Regent Idris and her shadar-kai keep these woods forever in shadow.

name: Unholy Pyre
description: Flames of undeath roar and crackle high into the night sky, celebrating the terror of The Drowned King.

name: Underdark Caverns
description: Many have tried to defeat Lord Jevahn Jhalvar and the drow that rule this area, but few return alive and none victorious.

name: Deep Mines
description: Duergar, led by Draghaz the Excavator, live and work within the deepest of the dark mines.

name: Magma Caves
description: Fiery creatures dwell amongst the rivers of magma that dominate this network of caves, each taking care not to anger Gommoth the Twisted.

name: The Feywild
description: Teeming with redcaps like Grimak Nailbiter, the feywild is not a place to be entered lightly.

name: Haunted Battlefield
description: Restless wights wander restlessly across this ancient battlefield, none deadlier than Bartholemew Blackdagger.

name: Wondrous Tomb
description: Bards tell of adventurers who visited this tomb and decided to stay with the dead.

name: Sunken City
description: Magical pockets of air allow adventurers to visit this aquatic tomb.

name: The Void
description: An impossible darkness flows from the mouth of the cave.

name: The Land of Dreams
description: A world unlocked only when dreaming.

name: Mythical Mines
description: Mines long-since dismissed as legend.

name: Demonic Cathedral
description: Unholy screams can be heard coming from this place of dark worship.

name: Dragon's Nest
description: Even the bravest adventurers have to think twice before approaching.

name: Twisting Nether
description: A place of corrupt magic, this journey is not for the faint of heart.

name: The Abyss
description: This could be a portal to another plane.

name: The Darkest Depths
description: A seemingly endless pit of hopelessness, legends tell of an ancient treasure hidden here.

name: The Arena
description: People from all walks of life brave the challenges found within the mysterious compound, each hoping to get a shot at Molly Redstone.

name: Giant Caverns
description: Massive rooms with towering ceilings serve to accommodate Magra Curse-Eye who dwells within.

name: City in the Underdark
description: Mindflayers are rumored to rule this city deep within the underdark, the horrible abomination Graft-Harrow at the forefront.

name: Slave Pens
description: Wizards and warriors of Thay, under the command of Xivros, use these slave pens as a place to properly train their thralls.

name: Defiled Woods
description: Wights and bone golems like Shatterspine swarm through the rotted trees, spreading their blight.

name: Orc Assault
description: The savage orcs of the Many-Arrows tribe are attacking the Neverwinter Guard Post! Gather your team to fight them off!

name: Straight to Helm
description: The Ashmadai occupying Helm's Hold plan to summon a devilish pit fiend from the Nine Hells! Heroes of all levels of skill are called to help stop them!

name: Pit Fight
description: The savage werewolves of the Gray Wolf barbarian tribe have issued a challenge to anyone who thinks they can survive their Totem Pit!
